
[1]wriggle

   WRIGGLE, v.i. To move the body to and fro with short motions.

   Both he and his successors would often wriggle in their seats, as long
   as the cushion lasted.

   WRIGGLE, v.t. To put into a quick reciprocating motion; to introduce by
                             a shifting motion.

   Wriggling his body to recover his seat, and cast his right leg over.
     __________________________________________________________________

